name: SHD Mobile COVID Vaccination Site
address: Stanwood Library - Sno-Isle Libraries, Stanwood WA, 98292
info:
*************THIS IS A PFIZER CLINIC********** 

Everyone 12 and older in Washington is eligible for COVID-19 vaccination. 

**Please also note that, 12 - 17 year olds, for the Pfizer vaccine, require a parent/guardian to physically be present to sign the consent form.**

Appointments are highly recommended but not required. Please arrive no more than 10 minutes prior to your appointment time. Expect to stay between 15-30 minutes after you receive your vaccine to monitor for any adverse reaction. Medical staff will be on hand. A mask must be worn at all times during the appointment, and please wear clothing with short or loose sleeves.
special: If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.

name: Thurston County Public Health Medical Reserve Corp
address: SPSCC 2011 Mottman Road SW, Olympia WA, 98512
info:
This is a Pfizer vaccination event for anyone age 12 and older.  

• This is a drive-thru clinic at South Puget Sound Community College (SPSCC), use the Crosby Blvd entrance. The clinic hours are 3:00PM - 7:00PM. • All minors 12 to 17 years old must receive parent or guardian consent to receive a COVID-19 vaccine. This must be done in PrepMod when registering for an appointment. Parents or guardians do not have to be present at the time of vaccination if they signed the consent form online during registration. • Please bring a form of identification with you to your appointment - ID card, passport, or other document with your name and birthday on it. • Wear a short-sleeved shirt, but dress with layers if necessary. • Please arrive at your scheduled appointment time. • Waiting at least 15 minutes after vaccination is required.
special: If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.
